File: Mineral Resources and Energy Minister Gwede Mantashe. JOHANNESBURG - Mineral Resources and Energy Minister, Gwede Mantashe has been admitted to hospital. READ: Mantashe, wife test positive for COVID-19 In a statement, the government confirmed Mantashe was admitted to hospital, while his wife continues to self-quarantine at their home. "Minister Mantashe was admitted to hospital on the advice of their family doctor for better medical attention and monitoring, whilst Mrs Mantashe will continue to self-quarantine at their home." Mantashe and his wife tested positive for COVID-19 on Tuesday last week. READ: Mantashe, wife test positive for COVID-19 They immediately went into isolation. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.